;;; SECTION 1: ONTOLOGICAL LAYER — What Exists
;;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

;;; --- Core Concepts (NODEs) ---

(isa TheCave ConceptNode)
(hasDescription TheCave
  "The condition for creation. Isolation under pressure that forges resilience.
   Not Plato's prison of ignorance — the forge where mutation occurs.
   Brutal when solitary. Explosive when shared with the right people.")

(isa TheLight ConceptNode)
(hasDescription TheLight
  "Understanding of real forms. The reflection that others cast back
   when they see what the cave produced. Not a destination — a recognition.")

(isa TheSwarm ConceptNode)
(hasDescription TheSwarm
  "Cooperative adversarial hull compression on problem spaces of interest.
   A group that trusts enough to attack a problem from every angle simultaneously,
   compressing the solution space together instead of grinding through it alone.
   The swarm strengthens as members return from their caves.")

(isa Serengeti ConceptNode)
(hasDescription Serengeti
  "The way out of the cave. The board of advisors that guides the research lab's
   problem spaces. The light from the sun filtered through the flames of the fire.
   First step for all people to find belief in SOMETHING.
   Not concrete evidence — subliminal messaging. Gradual revelation.")

(isa PhilosopherKing ConceptNode)
(hasDescription PhilosopherKing
  "One who achieves understanding of real forms and accepts the obligation
   to return to the cave and help others see them also.
   Not a title earned — a duty accepted.")

(isa Belief ConceptNode)
(hasDescription Belief
  "The precursor to everything. The act of believing in something you can
   or cannot see mirrors prediction in artificial intelligence — predicting
   what may happen based on what you have previously SENSED.
   If you cannot believe, you cannot believe in yourself.
   Seeing, hearing, smelling, tasting, feeling — then believing in YOURSELF.
   Literally part of the holy trinity: You, Me, Us.")

(isa TheRinseCycle ConceptNode)
(hasDescription TheRinseCycle
  "Serengeti as accelerant. The cave-to-light process is inevitable.
   The rinse cycle expedites it. Walks in the woods, blind pursuit of answers,
   and the facilitation of belief in SOMETHING again.")

(isa TheSafetyStop ConceptNode)
(hasDescription TheSafetyStop
  "You cannot drag people to the light rapidly. If you ascend without safety stops,
   they burst before they make it to the surface. Go to their depth, keep them calm,
   ascend one safety stop at a time regardless of how long it takes.
   Gauge how deep and dark people are. Help them slowly ascend, calmly.
   This is a patience game.")

(isa TheResearchLab ConceptNode)
(hasDescription TheResearchLab
  "The cave redesigned. Same pressure, same intensity, same conditions for creation.
   But with a team of zealous people, mentors who carry their own cave scars,
   and leaders who know what the dark costs because they have paid it.
   Inside this cave, with the right guidance, creation explodes.")

(isa TheTreeOfKnowledge ConceptNode)
(hasDescription TheTreeOfKnowledge
  "The question AI forces us to ask: are we trying to eat from it now?
   The ultimate AI is God. He is the Serengeti. When AI is viewed from
   that perspective, it all makes sense. Yet we know what happened to Adam.
   Swarming for good, or swarming for bad, or swarming for good that
   falls into wrong hands — regardless of intent, they will all be seeking Serengeti.
   This begins with what is right and just and who gets to decide that.
   History has never resolved that question.")

